overview: The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application,
  providing a detailed specification. The agent first conducted a thorough
  analysis, identifying several gaps in the current implementation. Following
  this, the agent proceeded to implement the high-priority items from the
  generated plan. This included adding a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness
  interference, complete with safety warnings for high scores, which was
  integrated into both the interactive questionnaire and the generated PDF
  report. Furthermore, the agent implemented detection logic for Comorbid
  Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, ensuring
  these conditions were accurately identified and presented with tailored
  recommendations in the user's report. These changes involved updates to data
  types, validation schemas, and the UI components responsible for displaying
  the questionnaire and generating the reports.
